Kfar HaRif (Hebrew: כְּפַר הָרִי"ף‎, lit. Village of the Rif) is a moshav in southern Israel. Located on the border of the Shephelah and the Israeli coastal plain around 2 kilometres northeast of Kiryat Malakhi, it is the largest community under the jurisdiction of Yoav Regional Council. In 2016 it had a population of 860.
The HaRif creek, named after the community, is located to the east of the village. Nearby are some wells.
